<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910313-0155</DOCNO><DOCID>910313-0155.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Denison Mines Ltd.:   Loss Is Reported for 1990   Following a Write-Down</HL><DATE>03/04/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   DEN.A</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)DIVERSIFIED MINING (MNG)</IN><LP>   Denison Mines Ltd., Toronto, reported a substantial 1990loss after writing down the value of its investment inDenison-Potacan Potash Co. by 116.5 million Canadian dollars(US$101.3 million).   Denison had a loss for the year of C$291.3 million, orC$4.83 a share, compared with a 1989 loss of C$4.3 million,or 47 Canadian cents a share. Revenue rose slightly toC$315.9 million from C$314.7 million.</LP><TEXT>   The company recently agreed to sell its 60% holding inDenison-Potacan, which had a book value of about C$160million, for C$15 million and the assumption of all itsDenison-Potacan related liabilities.   The loss for 1990 also included an C$82 million write-downof Denison's Koongarra uranium property in Australia, an C$80million write-down of its oil interests and a C$10.5 millionwrite-down of the company's long-term investments.</TEXT></DOC>